articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ guide for families
tripContent.description: "As a two-mom family who has been traveling to Orlando five to six times a year, we see the city like a second home. We absolutely love the theme parks but Orlando has so much more to offer! We love experiencing Orlando's rich diversity, fantastic food, incredible art and culture, plus a fun soccer game here and there. Join me, Allison Mertzman, as I share some of my family's favorite Orlando attractions with you!" - Allison Mertzman

tripContent.title: Celebrate Nevada's history, rhythm, and culture
tripContent.description: Nevada’s story is etched in historic mining towns, roadside wonders, galleries, and museums. From frontier heritage and atomic relics to glowing neon art, every stop reveals a new layer of the state's past and present. Whether you're wandering small-town streets or stepping into iconic city museums, this journey blends memory and motion in a way that’s anything but ordinary.

articleContent.title: Family fun in North Myrtle Beach: the ultimate trip planner

seoInfo.metaDescription: From laid-back beach days to sweet memories, find more of what your family loves in North Myrtle Beach. Its sun-drenched shores and easygoing pace offer a well-deserved break for always-on parents and busy kids.

articleContent.title: Discover the spirited soul of Bourbon City

seoInfo.metaDescription: Raise a glass to the charm of Louisville, Kentucky—a town with a rich history and a smooth bourbon scene, where each sip serves up a story of tradition and innovation. With iconic distilleries, exciting restaurants, and warm southern hospitality, Louisville’s authentic spirit is proof that the heart and soul of Bourbon City has aged to perfection.

seoInfo.metaDescription: Snorkel trips, beach days, and plenty of stand-out meals.

articleContent.title: 5 perfect days in New York City

seoInfo.metaDescription: More than 60 million people visit New York City every year, and a huge percentage of them only hit the big sites—Times Square, the Empire State Building, etc. I get it: They’re iconic. But as someone who has lived in this city for more than 30 years, I’m here to tell you that you’re missing out if you don’t mix in some off-the-beaten path locations. Luckily, five days gives you plenty of time to do just that.

We admit it: You can’t see everything London has to offer in just 48 hours. But with a strategic itinerary, you can get a surprisingly solid sense of England’s capital. From a taste of the royal life at Buckingham Palace to a taste of beer at a local pub, think of this as a London sampler.
